1. How is Aurora different from MySQL??
  a. adaptive thread pool. Autora is better.
  b. Online schema changes in Aurora. Transactional too. 
  c. query cache in aurora is good. 
  d. Claim upto 5 times faster.  
  e. Auto scales.
  f. HA and durabiliy automatic. Replicate  ways across 3 availability zones.
     An Aurora Replica, failover 30 seconds, otherwise 15 minutes. 

2. What else can auroa provide
   Aurora Serverless -- meant for infrequent tempoary use. 
   Aurora Parallel -- 2 orders of magnitude using many cpus. Transactional.
   	  a. No cost. cost is reading data from storage layer. 
   Aurora multi master - scale out, testing. 

