3. Expalain the normalizations. 
   1st: no sub columns, everthing in columns
   2nd: There is a key column, and non-key column depend on it
   3rd: all columns in parent table are keys or foriegn keys


4. Monitoring in RDS and Auraora
  1. Cloudwatch
     metrics -- view instance metrics
     alarms --- watch a mretic over time and alarm on it
     logs --- scan logs
  2. Enhanced monitiring metrics -- a lot of goodies of the OS and MySQL.
  3. amazon events -- like reboots, changes in variables. 
  4. Database Logs file


